8 pursuant to this Article are confidential and are not open to public inspection, except the
9 certificate of emancipation shall not be confidential. The petitioner, petitioner's attorney, an
10 appointed guardian ad litem, petitioner's parent, guardian, or custodian, and attorney of the
11 petitioner's parent, guardian, or custodian, may examine and obtain copies of the written parts of
12 the court record without an order of the court."
