28 MODIFY ROTATION OF SUPERIOR COURT JUDGES
29 SECTION 21.(a) G.S. 7A-47.3 is amended by adding a new subsection to read:
30 "(a1) In making assignment of the judges of the superior court for a district consisting of at
31 least one county with a population over 1,000,000 according to the most recent federal decennial
32 census, the Chief Justice of the Supreme Court shall include superior court judges from (i) other
33 districts in that same judicial division and (ii) districts from any judicial division adjacent to the
34 district consisting of at least one county with a population over 1,000,000. A superior court judge
35 from a district in an adjacent judicial division may only be assigned under the authorization set
36 forth in this subsection one six-month term every five years, except by consent of the judge. The
37 purpose of this subsection is to more evenly spread the burden placed on smaller judicial districts
38 from having judges who were elected for those districts holding court mostly in other judicial
39 districts consisting of larger counties."
40 SECTION 21.(b) This section is effective when it becomes law and applies to
41 rotations on or after that date.
